&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get to know Okta&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Okta is The World’s Identity Company. We free everyone to safely use any technology, anywhere, on any device or app. Our flexible and neutral products, Okta Platform and Auth0 Platform, provide secure access, authentication, and automation, placing identity at the core of business security and growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Okta, we celebrate a variety of perspectives and experiences. We are not looking for someone who checks every single box - we’re looking for lifelong learners and people who can make us better with their unique experiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Join our team! We’re building a world where Identity belongs to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Internship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for &lt;strong&gt;two&lt;/strong&gt; highly motivated and detail-oriented Events Marketing Interns to join and support the event charter of the Strategic Events and Experiences team, individuals responsible for executing world-class brand experiences, from our large-scale user conference &lt;strong&gt;Oktane &lt;/strong&gt;to third-party industry trade shows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will work closely with the Strategic Events and Experiences team and cross-functional stakeholders to bring our events to life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Get to Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management &amp;amp; Logistics: &lt;/strong&gt;Managing timelines, trackers, and deliverables to ensure our initiatives and programs run like clockwork&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Comms: &lt;/strong&gt;Support the creation of internal comms (such as internal newsletters, Slack updates, field overview guides, etc.) to drive company-wide alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audience Acquisition: &lt;/strong&gt;Support the execution of multi-channel campaigns to drive event attendance and monitor registration pacing and data to identify trends and help the team adjust strategy in real-time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Breakout Sessions &amp;amp; Content Logistics:&lt;/strong&gt; Support with speaker communications, deck collection, and session scheduling trackers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Technology &amp;amp; Infrastructure: &lt;/strong&gt;Support the testing and QA of the mobile event app and event website to capture elements that ensure a seamless attendee experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate with Strategic Events Marketing Managers and internal stakeholders across different time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current Enrollment:&lt;/strong&gt; Pursuing a degree in Marketing, Communications, Hospitality, or a related field with an expected graduation date of Dec. 2026 or May/June 2027&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The &quot;Event Brain&quot;:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple moving parts. You thrive on checklists and deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication Style:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional written and verbal communication. You can pivot from professional correspondence to punchy internal Slack updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; A &quot;no task is too small&quot; attitude and the flexibility to pivot when event plans change (because they always do).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech Savvy:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiarity with (or a strong desire to learn) marketing technology like &lt;strong&gt;Salesforce&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Marketo&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Slack&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;RainFocus/Cvent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Plus if you have:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior internship experience in marketing or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tips for Applying&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are tailoring your resume for this, emphasize any experience where you managed &lt;strong&gt;multiple moving parts&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., club leadership, previous internships, or hospitality experience). Okta loves candidates who show &quot;ownership&quot; and aren&#39;t afraid to dive into the data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;What you can look forward to as a Full-Time Okta employee!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Amazing &lt;a href=&quot;https://rewards.okta.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://rewards.okta.com/&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1677948559087000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw0Smv8KiGrXS3C1_LQmHF9D&quot;&gt;Benefits&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Making &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.okta.com/okta-for-good/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.okta.com/okta-for-good/&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1677948559087000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw2kKFyZVPp9NLrjKMOBXtWi&quot;&gt;Social Impact&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.okta.com/company/&quot;&gt;Talent and Fostering Connection + Community at Okta&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Okta cultivates a dynamic work environment, providing the best tools, technology and benefits to empower our employees to work productively in a setting that best and uniquely suits their needs. Each organization is unique in the degree of flexibility and mobility in which they work so that all employees are enabled to be their most creative and successful versions of themselves, regardless of where they live. Find your place at Okta&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.okta.com/company/careers/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.okta.com/company/careers/&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1677948559087000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw0Sy_6hHRhrwzwXgCfEiRV1&quot;&gt; today! &lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.okta.com/company/careers/&quot;&gt;https://www.okta.com/company/careers/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some roles may require travel to one of our office locations for in-person onboarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Okta is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, ancestry, marital status, age, physical or mental disability, or status as a protected veteran. We also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and convictions records, consistent with applicable laws. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If reasonable accommodation is needed to complete any part of the job application, interview process, or onboarding please use this&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1EfiEYZrIyhA2X4Fijk0R3RKYOzNoS3wtvyM4nhbZnXE/edit&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1EfiEYZrIyhA2X4Fijk0R3RKYOzNoS3wtvyM4nhbZnXE/edit&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1677948559087000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw152wP4kqe-oDJRAeGVJrN7&quot;&gt; Form&lt;/a&gt; to request an accommodation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notice for New York City Applicants &amp;amp; Employees:&lt;/strong&gt; Okta may use Automated Employment Decision Tools (AEDT), as defined by New York City Local Law 144, that use artificial intelligence, machine learning, or other automated processes to assist in our recruitment and hiring process. In accordance with NYC Local Law 144, if you are an applicant or employee residing in New York City, please &lt;a href=&quot;https://talent.okta.com/new-york-city-aedt-notice.html&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;click here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to view our full NYC AEDT Notice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Okta is committed to complying with applicable data privacy and security laws and regulations. For more information, please see our Personnel and Job Candidate Privacy Notice at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.okta.com/legal/personnel-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.okta.com/legal/personnel-policy/&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1759599734507000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw3KZGmq4Ud_Aq6tycXCiDeT&quot;&gt;https://www.okta.com/legal/personnel-policy/.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get to know Okta&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Okta is The World’s Identity Company. We free everyone to safely use any technology, anywhere, on any device or app. Our flexible and neutral products, Okta Platform and Auth0 Platform, provide secure access, authentication, and automation, placing identity at the core of business security and growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Okta, we celebrate a variety of perspectives and experiences. We are not looking for someone who checks every single box - we’re looking for lifelong learners and people who can make us better with their unique experiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Join our team! We’re building a world where Identity belongs to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Internship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a data-curious, detail-oriented Paid Media Intern to join our Digital Paid Media team. You won’t just be watching from the sidelines, you’ll be helping manage real budgets across Google, Bing, and LinkedIn. This is a &quot;hands on&quot; internship where you’ll learn the mechanics of digital advertising, from building campaigns to analyzing why an ad worked (or why it didn’t).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Get to Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Campaign Execution: Assist in the technical setup and launch of live campaigns across Google, Bing, and LinkedIn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative Coordination: Partner with the team to manage creative assets, ensuring we have the correct, up-to-date images and videos for every campaign.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad Copywriting &amp;amp; Auditing: Help manage our global paid search copy. You will write and review headlines and descriptions to ensure they are clear, follow Okta’s brand voice and guidelines, and stay within search engine character limits and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data &amp;amp; Reporting: Pull performance data into spreadsheets to help the team track key metrics like Cost per Click, Cost per Lead, and Conversion Rate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitor Research: Analyze competitor ads and keywords and market behavior to identify new opportunities for us to improve our search rankings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current Student: Enrolled in a Bachelor’s or Master’s program (Marketing, Business, Data Analytics, or Communications preferred) with an expected graduation date of either Dec. 2026 or May/June 2027.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software Basics: Proficient in Excel/Google Sheets (organizing data and basic formulas) and Google Slides (building clean, simple decks for team updates).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Writing: Ability to write clear and concise copy. You should be able to explain complex ideas in just a few words (essential for ad headlines).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Mindset: You enjoy looking at data to find patterns and are comfortable working with numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail: High level of accuracy in your work—you are the type of person who double-checks links and spelling before hitting &quot;send.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform Curiosity: A basic understanding of the difference between a &quot;paid&quot; search result and an &quot;organic&quot; one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational Skills: Ability to manage multiple small tasks and deadlines at once without losing track of progress.&lt;/li&gt;
